        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 6 at 6:45AM CDT until July 6 at 9:45AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive
rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...A portion of north central Texas, including the following
counties, Hood and Johnson.

* WHEN...Until 945 AM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Some low-water crossings may become impassable.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. This
will likely cause urban and small stream flooding. Low lying
and/or poor drainage areas will experience minor flooding in
the advisory area. Between 1 and 2 inches of rain have
fallen. Additional rainfall amounts of 1 to 2 inches are
forecast.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Granbury, Pecan Plantation, Godley, Oak Trail Shores, Squaw
Creek Reservoir, DeCordova, Cresson, Stockton Bend, Waples,
Mambrino, Acton and Lake Granbury.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
